        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    A sister or 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        a
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    brother can never, unless indeed such 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        symptoms
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    have been 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        shown
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        early,
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    suspect the other of fraud or false  
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        dealing,
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    when another 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        friend,
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    however strongly he may be 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        attached, may, in spite of himself, be
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        contemplated
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        with
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    suspicion. But I enjoyed 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        friends,
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    dear not only 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        &lt;pb xml:id="F1823_v2_524" n="251"/&gt;through habit and association,
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    but 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        from
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    their 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        own merits; and
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    wherever I 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        am,
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    the soothing voice of my 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        Elizabeth, and
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    the conversation of 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        Clerval,
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    will be ever whispered 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        in
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    my ear. They are  
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        dead;
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    and but one feeling 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        in such a
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        solitude
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        can
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    persuade me to preserve my life. If I 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        were
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    engaged in any high undertaking or 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        design,
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    fraught with extensive utility to my 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        fellow-creatures,
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    then could I live to fulfil 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        it. But
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    such is not my 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        destiny; I
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    must pursue and destroy the 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        being
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    to whom I gave  
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        existence;
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    then my 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        lot on earth
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    will be 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        fulfilled,
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_end"/&gt;
    and I may 
        &lt;seg xml:id="{ancestor::app/@xml:id}-{@wit}_start"/&gt;
        die.” &lt;p eID="novel1_letter4_div4_p46"/&gt;
